Number = {4},
Pages = {594-601},
Month = {OCT},
Abstract = {Pristiphora fructicola Smith and Dolan, n. sp., is described from
   Montana. It would belong to the former genus Melastola Wong of the
   former tribe Pristolini, recently synonymized with Pristiphora
   Latreille. Adults were numerous around Vaccinium globulare Rydberg
   (Ericaceae), the presumed host, where larvae feed in the fruits. The
   species is distinguished from the other two species previously placed in
   Melastola, P. resinicolor (Marlatt) and P. ferruginosa (Wong) (n.
   comb.). Several new distribution records and host plant associations are
   given for the species of ``Pristolini.{''}},
